[ Civ. No. 18580. Second Dist., Div. One. Mar. 26, 1952.] HERBERT ROSENBERG, Appellant, v. EMANUEL V. FEIGIN, Respondent. Edward B. Freed for Appellant.

Ralph N. Highsmith and Henry E. Kappier for Respondent.

HANSON, J. pro tem.

The appeal is from an order denying a motion to set aside a ruling which sustained a to the third amended complaint. The order is not an appealable order (Code Civ. Proc., § 963; Title Ins. & Trust Co. v. California Dev. Co., 159 Cal. 484 [114 P. 838]).

The appeal is dismissed.

White, P. J., and Doran, J., concurred.
